<subSubSection id="CF31F4289DAA0B0CE1BBA4FEFB9E1A7E" pageId="17" pageNumber="110" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="68FD9958D54BC7EC1DCBCFF0C5B5DCB6" pageId="17" pageNumber="110">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6CC5E37FBC90075ABE9D2D0D82127508" pageId="17" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName id="92532E8EDE61986003EA8E1998A863C8" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella potaroensis" order="Selaginellales" pageId="17" pageNumber="110" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="potaroensis">
<emphasis id="A39265B788D7317F18B8302C1C8CD85E" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="110">Selaginella potaroensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously known to occur in Venezuela, Guyana, Suriname, and French Guiana (
<bibRefCitation id="3B1640E2C2E7B5C28BC02074A6244F1E" author="Alston, AHG" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Botany" pageId="19" pageNumber="112" pagination="233 - 330" refId="B2" refString="Alston, AHG, Jermy, AC, Rankin, JM, 1981. The genus Selaginella in tropical South America. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Botany 9: 233 - 330" title="The genus Selaginella in tropical South America." volume="9" year="1981">Alston et al. 1981</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="A8544B05FF65AC857AABCC86E8DB8DFB" author="Smith, AR" journalOrPublisher="Pteridophytes, Spermatophytes: Acanthaceae-Araceae" pageId="21" pageNumber="114" pagination="296 - 314" refId="B25" refString="Smith, AR, 1995. Selaginellaceae. Pteridophytes, Spermatophytes: Acanthaceae-Araceae Vol. 2: 296 - 314" title="Selaginellaceae." volume="Vol. 2" year="1995">Smith 1995</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="068049B7F622D597978E735E432635E8" author="Cremers, G" editor="Funk, V" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the United States National Herbarium" pageId="19" pageNumber="112" pagination="17 - 56" refId="B4" refString="Cremers, G, Hickey, RJ, Lellinger, DB, Mickel, JT, Moran, RC, Ollgaard, B, Smith, AR, 2007. Pteridophytes &amp; allies. In: Funk, V, Hollowell, T, Berry, P, Kelloff, C, Alexander, SN, Eds., Checklist of the plants of the Guiana Shield (Venezuela: Amazonas, Bolivar, Delta Amacuro; Guyana, Surinam, French Guiana). Contributions from the United States National Herbarium 55: 17 - 56" title="Pteridophytes &amp; allies." volume="55" volumeTitle="Checklist of the plants of the Guiana Shield (Venezuela: Amazonas, Bolivar, Delta Amacuro; Guyana, Surinam, French Guiana)." year="2007">Cremers et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
). Its range is documented here northward to include Costa Rica (see 
<bibRefCitation id="54B99DC8398A1D52B7E220CD00DB1507" author="Tropicos ®" journalOrPublisher="Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="21" pageNumber="114" publicationUrl="http://www.tropicos.org/Name/40034882" refId="B29" refString="Tropicos®, 2015b. Manual de plantas de Costa Rica. Tropicos.org. Missouri Botanical Garden, http://www.tropicos.org/Name/40034882 [accessed 27.08.2015]" title="Manual de plantas de Costa Rica. Tropicos. org" url="http://www.tropicos.org/Name/40034882" year="2015 b">Tropicos 2015b</bibRefCitation>
), and it is to be expected in Panama and Colombia. This species is also known from Brazil.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="28D3AF9376F26C287854BC39607C7C1E" pageId="17" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName id="28EE90168A5C47E940A2F067DB588DD3" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella potaroensis" order="Selaginellales" pageId="17" pageNumber="110" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="potaroensis">
<emphasis id="B3BAA11BB420F3D3C09F4B670F869198" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="110">Selaginella potaroensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a creeping plant characterized by having axillary rhizophores throughout the stems, membranaceous leaves, the median leaves semicordate to ovate with the outer half of the lamina almost twice as wide as the inner one, margins hyaline and denticulate with the outer margin convex and the inner one almost straight, laminae abruptly tapering into a long-acuminate apex with conspicuous stomata on the upper surface, the lateral leaves ovate-elliptic with minute submarginal teeth along the upper surfaces of basiscopic halves, and acute apices tipped by 1-3 teeth. The similarities and differences of 
<taxonomicName id="C7EC5C7755875DAE7A553EDF64712413" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella potaroensis" order="Selaginellales" pageId="17" pageNumber="110" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="potaroensis">
<emphasis id="FAF7FC56C5C4DADCAD879CE21D0A8777" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="110">Selaginella potaroensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="159EB7F270E7D865776761FD145E7C2D" authorityName="Valdespino" authorityYear="1992" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella cardiophylla" order="Selaginellales" pageId="17" pageNumber="110" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="cardiophylla">
<emphasis id="0561DB3CE691CD87B055DFCA94427F87" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="110">Selaginella cardiophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="689B7CB418869C49F848847F9E653226" authorityName="Valdespino" authorityYear="1992" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella hemicardia" order="Selaginellales" pageId="17" pageNumber="110" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="hemicardia">
<emphasis id="9922FB614E170B297A3EC24848E13C7E" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="110">Selaginella hemicardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4727064C36B9E2AF9768239CB4CAB883" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella rhodostachya" order="Selaginellales" pageId="17" pageNumber="110" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="rhodostachya">
<emphasis id="9A26B26D9E748FA39ACF218816D6549D" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="110">Selaginella rhodostachya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Baker are discussed in 
<bibRefCitation id="4A14942A929D91758CF9C660F2AB3762" author="Valdespino, IA" journalOrPublisher="Brittonia" pageId="21" pageNumber="114" pagination="199 - 207" publicationUrl="10.2307/2806833" refId="B30" refString="Valdespino, IA, 1992. New species of Selaginella (Selaginellaceae) from the Guayana Highland of Venezuela. Brittonia 44: 199 - 207, DOI: 10.2307/2806833" title="New species of Selaginella (Selaginellaceae) from the Guayana Highland of Venezuela." url="10.2307/2806833" volume="44" year="1992">Valdespino (1992)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
